  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you use Google Account Recovery to reset your password?",
  "response": "Resetting your Google Account password using the **Google Account Recovery** process is straightforward. Follow the step-by-step guide below to regain access to your account:\n\n### **Step 1: Go to the Google Account Recovery Page**\n\n- **Visit the Recovery Page:** Open your web browser and navigate to the [Google Account Recovery](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery) page.\n\n### **Step 2: Enter Your Email or Phone Number**\n\n- **Provide Your Information:** On the recovery page, enter the **email address** or **phone number** associated with your Google account.\n- **Click \"Next\":** After entering your information, click the **\"Next\"** button.\n\n### **Step 3: Verify Your Identity**\n\nGoogle will ask you to verify your identity to ensure that you are the rightful owner of the account. Depending on the information you've previously provided to Google, you might see one or more of the following options:\n\n1. **Enter the Last Password You Remember:**\n   - If prompted, enter the **last password** you recall using with your account.\n   - If you don't remember any, click **\"Try another way.\"**\n\n2. **Verification via Recovery Email or Phone:**\n   - **Recovery Email:** Google may send a verification code to your **recovery email address**. Access that email account, retrieve the code, and enter it when prompted.\n   - **Recovery Phone:** Alternatively, Google might send a **text message** or **call** your recovery phone number with a verification code. Enter the code when prompted.\n\n3. **Answer Security Questions:**\n   - If you've set up security questions, Google might ask you to answer them. Provide accurate answers to proceed.\n\n4. **Use a Trusted Device:**\n   - If you're on a device (like your smartphone or laptop) that you've frequently used to access your Google account, it may recognize it and allow you to proceed without additional verification.\n\n### **Step 4: Create a New Password**\n\n- **Enter New Password:** Once your identity is verified, you'll be prompted to **enter a new password**. Make sure it's strong and unique, combining letters (both uppercase and lowercase), numbers, and special characters.\n  \n- **Confirm New Password:** Re-enter the new password to confirm.\n\n### **Step 5: Complete the Recovery Process**\n\n- **Password Reset Confirmation:** After successfully setting your new password, you'll receive a confirmation message indicating that your password has been changed.\n  \n- **Sign In:** You can now sign in to your Google account using your new password.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Use a Device and Location You\u2019ve Used Before:** Performing the recovery process on a device (like your smartphone or laptop) and in a location (like your home or office) where you've previously accessed your account can make verification easier.\n\n- **Keep Recovery Information Updated:** To prevent future access issues, ensure your **recovery email address** and **phone number** are always up-to-date in your Google Account settings.\n\n- **Use a Strong, Unique Password:** Consider using a password manager to generate and store complex passwords, enhancing your account's security.\n\n- **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):** Adding an extra layer of security can help protect your account from unauthorized access. You can set this up in your Google Account settings.\n\n### **If You\u2019re Unable to Recover Your Account:**\n\nIf you\u2019ve tried all available recovery options and still can\u2019t access your account:\n\n1. **Visit the [Account Recovery Help Page](https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/7682439):** This page provides additional guidance and troubleshooting steps.\n   \n2. **Fill Out the Account Recovery Form:** Provide as much accurate information as possible to help Google verify your identity.\n\n3. **Wait for Google's Response:** It may take several days for Google to review your account recovery request.\n\n### **Prevent Future Access Issues:**\n\n- **Regularly Update Recovery Information:** Periodically check and update your recovery email and phone number.\n  \n- **Review Security Settings:** Use Google's [Security Checkup](https://myaccount.google.com/security-checkup) to review your account's security settings and recent activity.\n\nBy following these steps and maintaining good security practices, you can effectively manage and recover your Google Account when needed.",
